{"type":"message","id":"8dec0c85","parentId":"9f244f1f","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:01:43.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the context, Zach said \"continue building this\" after I had scaffolded the CodeCause project and tested the causal indexer. The project is already scaffolded and the causal indexer is working (it built graphs for code-cause, temporal-attention, and EXP). \n\nThe remaining issue is that the query engine's entity extraction doesn't work well with dotted paths like \"src.causal_indexer.CausalGraph\" - it needs exact names or quotes.\n\nLet me continue by fixing the query engine entity extraction bug, then committing the work. I can see from the conversation that:\n1. The static analyzer and graph builder are working\n2. The query engine's entity extraction is broken (can't extract entities from dotted paths without quotes)\n\n\n3. I need to fix the entity extraction logic to handle dotted names properly, then test it on a real codebase before committing everything.","thinkingSignature":"415b945eee24abc6717e14a3b6a7eba3643817eedea992d3f48faa3cabf0cca5"},{"type":"text","text":"Fixing the query engine entity extraction first — that's the last broken piece.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j9v918a54wgz_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":1,"limit":60,"file_path":"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\causal_indexer\\query_engine.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":253,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":22401,"totalTokens":35316,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774216893523}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d7e6130","parentId":"8dec0c85","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:01:43.031Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_j9v918a54wgz_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nQuery Engine\n============\nHigh-level causal queries over the dependency graph.\n\nProvides natural-language-style queries that map to graph traversals,\nplus ranking/filtering of results.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Optional\nfrom .graph_builder import CausalGraph\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass CausalResult:\n    \"\"\"A single result from a causal query.\"\"\"\n    entity: str\n    kind: str\n    file_path: str\n    lineno: int\n    docstring: Optional[str]\n    score: float            # importance/relevance score\n    path: list[str]        # causal path from query root to this entity\n    reason: str            # human-readable explanation of why this matters\n\n\nclass QueryEngine:\n    \"\"\"\n    Causal query interface for a codebase graph.\n\n    Example:\n        engine = QueryEngine(graph)\n        results = engine.query(\"what happens if I change auth.py validate_token?\")\n        for r in results:\n            print(f\"{r.entity} (score={r.score:.2f}): {r.reason}\")\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, graph: CausalGraph):\n        self.graph = graph\n\n    def query(self, question: str, top_k: int = 10) -> list[CausalResult]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Parse a natural-ish question and execute the corresponding causal query.\n\n        Supported question patterns:\n        - \"what happens if I change X?\" / \"what does X affect?\" / \"impact of X\"\n        - \"what caused X?\" / \"what does X depend on?\" / \"causes of X\"\n        - \"what uses X?\" / \"who calls X?\" / \"dependents of X\"\n        - \"ripple effect of X\" / \"full impact of X\"\n        \"\"\"\n        q = question.lower()\n\n        # Extract entity name from quotes or \"of X\" pattern\n        entity = self._extract_entity(q)\n\n        if any(k in q for k in [\"affect\", \"impact\", \"happens if\", \"changes\", \"ripple\", \"break\", \"what will\"]):\n            return self._query_impact(entity, top_k)\n\n[246 more lines in file. Use offset=61 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774216903023}}
{"type":"message","id":"e3c1c1e0","parentId":"6d7e6130","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:01:46.044Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the `_extract_entity` method and the part that handles dotted paths.","thinkingSignature":"36f31ddee9d0dcaa5fddabf5a45a30a906f0e128067491b93cbc1d003aea8f48"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qyckj48ia11k_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":61,"limit":80,"file_path":"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\causal_indexer\\query_engine.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23175,"output":79,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35873,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774216903032}}
{"type":"message","id":"281116bf","parentId":"e3c1c1e0","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:01:46.062Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qyckj48ia11k_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        elif any(k in q for k in [\"caus\", \"depend\", \"prereq\", \"needed\", \"what does x need\"]):\n            return self._query_causes(entity, top_k)\n        elif any(k in q for k in [\"uses\", \"calls\", \"who\", \"dependents\", \"what uses\"]):\n            return self._query_dependents(entity, top_k)\n        else:\n            # Default to impact query\n            return self._query_impact(entity, top_k)\n\n    def _extract_entity(self, question: str) -> Optional[str]:\n        \"\"\"Extract the entity being asked about from the question text.\"\"\"\n        import re\n\n        # Match quoted strings: \"auth.validate_token\" or 'auth.validate_token'\n        quoted = re.findall(r'[\"\\']([^\"\\']+)[\"\\']', question)\n        if quoted:\n            return quoted[0]\n\n        # Match \"of X\" pattern: \"of auth.validate_token\"\n        of_match = re.search(r'\\bof\\s+([\\w.]+)', question)\n        if of_match:\n            return of_match.group(1)\n\n        # Match \"change X\" / \"modify X\" / \"affect X\"\n        modify_match = re.search(r'(?:change|modify|affect|update|edit)\\s+([\\w.]+)', question)\n        if modify_match:\n            return modify_match.group(1)\n\n        return None\n\n    def _score_result(self, name: str, depth: int, is_interface: bool, edge_kind: str) -> float:\n        \"\"\"\n        Score a query result by importance.\n        Higher score = more important to consider.\n        \"\"\"\n        score = 1.0\n\n        # Depth penalty: shallow impacts matter more\n        score -= depth * 0.15\n\n        # Interface bonus: things with many dependents are critical\n        if is_interface:\n            score += 0.5\n\n        # Entry point bonus\n        node = self.graph.nodes.get(name)\n        if node and node.is_entry_point:\n            score += 0.4\n\n        # Edge kind weighting\n        if edge_kind == \"calls\":\n            score += 0.1\n        elif edge_kind == \"inherits\":\n            score += 0.2\n        elif edge_kind == \"imports\":\n            score -= 0.1\n\n        # External nodes are less interesting\n        if node and node.kind == \"external\":\n            score -= 0.3\n\n        return max(0.0, score)\n\n    def _query_impact(self, entity: Optional[str], top_k: int) -> list[CausalResult]:\n        \"\"\"What changes if I modify this entity?\"\"\"\n        if not entity:\n            return []\n\n        # Try exact match first, then fuzzy\n        target = self._resolve_entity(entity)\n        if not target:\n            return []\n\n        impacts = self.graph.query_impact(target, depth=5)\n        results = []\n\n        for imp in impacts[:top_k * 2]:  # over-fetch for scoring\n            node_data = imp[\"node\"]\n            score = self._score_result(\n                imp[\"name\"],\n                imp[\"depth\"],\n\n[166 more lines in file. Use offset=141 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774216906055}}
{"type":"message","id":"014f00d1","parentId":"281116bf","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:02:04.281Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is in `_extract_entity`. The regex for \"of X\" and \"change X\" uses `[\\w.]+` which should match dotted paths, but there's a problem: `\\w` only matches `[a-zA-Z0-9_]` — it doesn't match hyphens. However, the bigger issue is that the regex `\\bof\\s+([\\w.]+)` would match `of src.causal_indexer.CausalGraph` but might not work well with `of X.Y` patterns.\n\nLet me look at the actual problem: when I queried `what happens if I change src.causal_indexer.CausalGraph.from_analysis?`, the entity extraction returned `None`. The regex for `change X` would be: `r'(?:change|modify|affect|update|edit)\\s+([\\w.]+)'` on `what happens if i change src.causal_indexer.CausalGraph.from_analysis?`. \n\nThe regex should match `src.causal_indexer.CausalGraph.from_analysis` since it contains word characters and dots, but not underscores or hyphens. I need to check whether the incoming question is being lowercased and if that affects the pattern matching, and also trace through what `_resolve_entity` does when it receives this extracted entity.\n\nWhen I tested with `\"src.causal_indexer.CausalGraph\"`, the entity resolved to `.src.causal_indexer.CausalGraph` with no impact count, but when testing `EventBasedStore._apply_focus_decay`, it didn't resolve at all. The issue might be that the entity string starts with a dot in some cases, which could be coming from how the analyzer constructs qualified names when processing files in different directories.\n\nLooking at the code flow, the graph is being queried with `.EventBasedStore._apply_focus_decay` (note the leading dot), but the actual node name stored might be `EventBasedStore._apply_focus_decay` without that leading dot. So I need to strip leading dots when resolving entities. For the EXP graph, the `kv_evict.BlockManager` reference is being resolved as `apps.kv_eviction_optimizer.kv_evict.BlockManager` but `apps.kv_eviction_optimizer.examples.main` has zero incoming edges even though it should be calling BlockManager based on the test output showing references like `apps.kv_eviction_optimizer.examples.main. --[call]--> kv_evict.BlockManager`.\n\nThe issue is that these references to `kv_evict.BlockManager` (unqualified) are being treated as external nodes rather than resolving to the actual `apps.kv_eviction_optimizer.kv_evict.BlockManager` definition, which is why the query returns zero results.\n\nTo fix the immediate problems: I need to strip leading dots from resolved entity names in the query engine, and add a fallback resolution step that tries stripping module prefixes when an exact match isn't found. Let me implement these fixes and test on the temporal-attention codebase where the issue is most apparent.","thinkingSignature":"629a3295d2ffce48b37d0c602a9f43d2e690fae6e167df9e8faf5f6b85bbf581"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tj13qjo17ao6_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":90,"limit":50,"file_path":"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\causal_indexer\\graph_builder.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23943,"output":680,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37242,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774216906063}}
