{"type":"message","id":"8b5229a0","parentId":"5369de24","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:02:48.373Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9bs97y473z23_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    def _extract_entity(self, question: str) -> Optional[str]:\n        \"\"\"Extract the entity being asked about from the question text.\"\"\"\n        import re\n\n        # Match quoted strings: \"auth.validate_token\" or 'auth.validate_token'\n        quoted = re.findall(r'[\"\\']([^\"\\']+)[\"\\']', question)\n        if quoted:\n            return quoted[0]\n\n        # Match \"of X\" pattern: \"of auth.validate_token\"\n        of_match = re.search(r'\\bof\\s+([\\w.]+)', question)\n        if of_match:\n            return of_match.group(1)\n\n        # Match \"change X\" / \"modify X\" / \"affect X\"\n        modify_match = re.search(r'(?:change|modify|affect|update|edit)\\s+([\\w.]+)', question)\n        if modify_match:\n            return modify_match.group(1)\n\n        return None\n\n[230 more lines in file. Use offset=89 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774216968363}}
{"type":"message","id":"c932c6bb","parentId":"8b5229a0","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:03:04.226Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `_extract_entity` method uses `[\\w.]+` which doesn't match hyphens, but also uses `question.lower()`. However, it doesn't strip question marks or parentheses, so when I query `what happens if I change src.causal_indexer.CausalGraph.from_analysis?`, the `?` at the end gets included in the entity extraction if it follows a word character. Let me check: `r'(?:change|modify|affect|update|edit)\\s+([\\w.]+)'` would match `change src.causal_indexer.CausalGraph.from_analysis` but stop at the `?`. Since `?` is not in `[\\w.]`, it would stop at `.from_analysis` and capture the right entity.\n \nTracing through the regex more carefully, `[\\w.]+` captures word characters and dots greedily, so `src.causal_indexer.CausalGraph.from_analysis` gets matched completely before hitting the `?`. The issue might actually be that the query contains a leading dot or something else interfering with the matching. The regex pattern `[\\w.]+` actually matches dots as part of the character class, so it should correctly capture `src.causal_indexer.CausalGraph.from_analysis` up until the `?`. The real issue is likely in the subsequent `_resolve_entity` lookup rather than the extraction itself. I'm realizing the query was sent through the debug script without the `?` at the end, so the entity extraction should work correctly. Let me test this with a cleaner approach that handles both the `change X` pattern and the `of X` pattern, then run a test on the temporal-attention codebase.","thinkingSignature":"067bea08245103e173bfdd2a5ce3723fa071b9c5663ce6f3ae185bbf4ac3c0d7"},{"type":"text","text":"Now test on temporal-attention with the fixes:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h0bm3cjcymms_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:/dev/code-cause && python -c \"\nimport sys; sys.path.insert(0, 'src')\nfrom causal_indexer import StaticAnalyzer, CausalGraph, QueryEngine\nimport json\n\n# Test on temporal-attention\nanalyzer = StaticAnalyzer('C:/dev/temporal-attention')\nanalyzer.analyze()\ngraph = CausalGraph.from_analysis(analyzer.definitions, analyzer.references)\n\n# Test query\nengine = QueryEngine(graph)\n\ntests = [\n    'what happens if I change EventBasedStore._apply_focus_decay?',\n    'what happens if I change FocusDecay?',\n    'what does EventBasedStore affect?',\n    'what affects FocusDecay?',\n]\n\nfor t in tests:\n    print(f'Q: {t}')\n    results = engine.query(t, top_k=5)\n    print(f'  -> {len(results)} results')\n    for r in results[:3]:\n        print(f'     [{r.kind}] {r.entity} (score={r.score:.2f})')\n    print()\n\" 2>&1","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":28397,"output":611,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41627,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774216968375}}
