{"type":"message","id":"c1a939eb","parentId":"0dbecd94","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:03:44.421Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue. The node names have a leading dot! For example `.detect_2x2`, `.EventBasedStore._apply_focus_decay`. This is because the module name is empty (files in the root directory), so when building the qualified name from a file like `temporal_attention/core.py`, the module name is empty, and the qualified name starts with a dot.\n\nThis is a design issue in the static analyzer. When the module is empty/root-level, the qualified name shouldn't start with a dot.\n\nThe fix could be:\n1. Fix the static analyzer to not add leading dots for empty modules\n\n\n2. Or handle this in the graph builder and query engine\n\nThe most robust approach would be to fix the root cause in the static analyzer itself. When `_module_stack` is empty, I should skip the dot prefix entirely rather than prepending it to everything.\n\nIn the analyzer, when constructing the qualified name from a file at the root level, it's creating `.method_name` for things like `core.py::class Method`. Instead of prefixing with a dot when there's no parent module, I can just use the method name directly.\n\nThe issue is that `_module_stack` gets appended to even when there are no parent directories, resulting in `['']` which then joins into an empty string with a dot prefix. I need to check if the module name is actually empty before adding the leading dot.\n\nThe cleanest solution is to modify how I join the module name with the basename—skip the dot entirely when there's no module namespace.","thinkingSignature":"88ce8915320585b3ebd5d51fa726c01936f3aed79c28f6b3727f95e9b6b85faa"},{"type":"text","text":"Found it — nodes have leading dots because root-level modules produce empty qualified names. Fix the static analyzer:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d87q2m95doe3_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":100,"limit":60,"file_path":"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\causal_indexer\\static_analyzer.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30490,"output":401,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43510,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774217012396}}
{"type":"message","id":"49725229","parentId":"c1a939eb","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:03:44.445Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d87q2m95doe3_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    def get_module_qualname(self, module_path: str, name: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Build fully qualified name: e.g. 'mypackage.submodule.func'\"\"\"\n        prefix = f\"{module_path}.\" if module_path else \"\"\n        return f\"{prefix}{name}\"\n\n\nclass DefinitionVisitor(ast.NodeVisitor):\n    \"\"\"Collects definitions and references from an AST.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, module_name: str, file_path: str):\n        self.module_name = module_name\n        self.file_path = file_path\n        self.definitions: list[Definition] = []\n        self.references: list[Reference] = []\n        self._class_stack: list[str] = []  # nested class context\n        self._scope: list[str] = []        # current qualified path\n\n    def _qualname(self, name: str) -> str:\n        parts = [self.module_name] + self._scope + [name]\n        return \".\".join(parts)\n\n    def visit_Module(self, node: ast.Module) -> None:\n        self.generic_visit(node)\n\n    def visit_ClassDef(self, node: ast.ClassDef) -> None:\n        qualname = self._qualname(node.name)\n        self._class_stack.append(node.name)\n        self._scope.append(node.name)\n\n        # Inheritance references\n        for base in node.bases:\n            self._record_ref(base, \"inherit\", \"inherit\")\n\n        # Decorators\n        for dec in node.decorator_list:\n            self._record_ref(dec, \"attribute\", \"decorator\")\n\n        self.definitions.append(Definition(\n            name=node.name,\n            fully_qualified=qualname,\n            kind=\"class\",\n            file_path=self.file_path,\n            lineno=node.lineno or 0,\n            end_lineno=node.end_lineno,\n            docstring=ast.get_docstring(node),\n            decorators=[self._get_name(d) for d in node.decorator_list],\n        ))\n\n        self.generic_visit(node)\n        self._scope.pop()\n        self._class_stack.pop()\n\n    def visit_FunctionDef(self, node: ast.FunctionDef) -> None:\n        self._add_function(node, \"function\")\n\n    def visit_AsyncFunctionDef(self, node: ast.AsyncFunctionDef) -> None:\n        self._add_function(node, \"function\", is_async=True)\n\n    def _add_function(self, node: ast.FunctionDef | ast.AsyncFunctionDef, kind: str, is_async: bool = False) -> None:\n        qualname = self._qualname(node.name)\n\n[239 more lines in file. Use offset=160 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774217024437}}
