{"type":"message","id":"b2bac6cc","parentId":"413f9370","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:05:06.913Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The \"what calls\" and \"what uses\" patterns are failing because they're checking for keywords in the query. Let me look at the query method again to understand what patterns trigger what queries. Also \"EventBasedStore\" alone returns 0 results because there's no keyword trigger for \"what does X affect\" type queries.\n\nLet me look at the query patterns more carefully. From the code:\n\n```python\nif any(k in q for k in [\"affect\", \"impact\", \"happens if\", \"changes\", \"ripple\", \"break\", \"what will\"]):\n    return self._query_impact(entity, top_k)\nelif any(k in q for k in [\"caus\", \"depend\", \"prereq\", \"needed\", \"what does x need\"]):\n\n\n```\n\nThe real issue is that when someone asks \"what calls EventBasedStore._apply_focus_decay\", the keyword matching for \"uses\" and \"calls\" isn't being triggered, so it's falling through to the default `_query_impact` instead of routing to `_query_dependents`. The keyword \"uses\" needs to be added to the second condition to properly match queries about function callers.\n\n```","thinkingSignature":"f01f4bf9d0883492936e7ece6a044aeed504f797f3df54adde268e223283cae9"},{"type":"text","text":"\nThe issue is the query type routing — \"uses\" and \"calls\" aren't triggering `_query_dependents`. Let me fix the routing:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dp3c1jued5z4_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":39,"limit":20,"file_path":"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\causal_indexer\\query_engine.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34500,"output":330,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47449,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774217097947}}
{"type":"message","id":"69205ce4","parentId":"b2bac6cc","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:05:06.936Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_dp3c1jued5z4_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, graph: CausalGraph):\n        self.graph = graph\n\n    def query(self, question: str, top_k: int = 10) -> list[CausalResult]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Parse a natural-ish question and execute the corresponding causal query.\n\n        Supported question patterns:\n        - \"what happens if I change X?\" / \"what does X affect?\" / \"impact of X\"\n        - \"what caused X?\" / \"what does X depend on?\" / \"causes of X\"\n        - \"what uses X?\" / \"who calls X?\" / \"dependents of X\"\n        - \"ripple effect of X\" / \"full impact of X\"\n        \"\"\"\n        q = question.lower()\n\n        # Extract entity name from quotes or \"of X\" pattern\n        entity = self._extract_entity(q)\n\n\n[260 more lines in file. Use offset=59 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774217106926}}
{"type":"message","id":"205a7b9b","parentId":"69205ce4","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:05:30.458Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `_extract_entity` receives `question.lower()` but the entity extraction regex uses `[\\w.]+` which doesn't match uppercase letters. Since the question is lowercased, `EventBasedStore` becomes `eventbasedstore` and then the resolution works (case-insensitive). But wait, the issue might be in `_extract_entity` itself — it receives the lowercased question and tries to extract the entity.\n\nLet me trace through `_extract_entity` for `q = \"what happens if I change EventBasedStore._apply_focus_decay\".lower()`:\n- `quoted = []` — no quotes\n\n\n- `of_match` — no \"of X\" pattern\n- `modify_match = re.search(r'(?:change|modify|affect|update|edit)\\s+([\\w.]+)', q)` → `eventbasedstore._apply_focus_decay`\n\nSo `_extract_entity` correctly extracts `eventbasedstore._apply_focus_decay`. Then `_query_impact` is called because the question contains \"change\". But the problem is the question contains \"change\" which routes to `_query_impact` when it should route to `_query_dependents` since the user is asking \"what calls this function?\" not \"what does this function affect?\".\n\nThe real issue is that \"what happens if I change X?\" and \"what does X affect?\" both trigger `_query_impact`, but they mean different things — one asks about dependents (who's affected by changing X) and the other asks about what X depends on. The keywords need better disambiguation to route to the right query type. not about dependencies.\n\nI think the cleanest fix is to distinguish based on question structure: if the question asks \"what happens if I change X\" or \"what will change if I modify X\", that's asking for impact on other code. But \"what does X affect\" is ambiguous—it could mean either what X impacts or what X depends on. The real issue is that \"what does EventBasedStore affect\" should route to `_query_impact`, but \"what uses EventBasedStore\" should route to `_query_dependents`. The \"uses/calls\" keywords should take precedence over generic \"affect\" keywords. Let me restructure the routing logic to handle these patterns more carefully.","thinkingSignature":"d86e9385e97806b103fc94d52ae36e87a5ca9010e2cda5bb85da4571711ced19"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aocx97oci5tz_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\causal_indexer\\query_engine.py","old_string":"        q = question.lower()\n\n        # Extract entity name from quotes or \"of X\" pattern\n        entity = self._extract_entity(q)\n\n        if any(k in q for k in [\"affect\", \"impact\", \"happens if\", \"changes\", \"ripple\", \"break\", \"what will\"]):\n            return self._query_impact(entity, top_k)\n        elif any(k in q for k in [\"caus\", \"depend\", \"prereq\", \"needed\", \"what does x need\"]):\n            return self._query_causes(entity, top_k)\n        elif any(k in q for k in [\"uses\", \"calls\", \"who\", \"dependents\", \"what uses\"]):\n            return self._query_dependents(entity, top_k)\n        else:\n            # Default to impact query\n            return self._query_impact(entity, top_k)","new_string":"        q = question.lower()\n\n        # Extract entity name from quotes or \"of X\" pattern\n        entity = self._extract_entity(q)\n\n        # \"what calls X\" / \"who uses X\" → dependents (who depends on X)\n        if any(k in q for k in [\"calls\", \"who calls\", \"who use\", \"what calls\", \"dependents\", \"who depend\"]):\n            return self._query_dependents(entity, top_k)\n        # \"what does X affect\" / \"what will break if X changes\" → impact (what X touches)\n        elif any(k in q for k in [\"affect\", \"ripple\", \"break\", \"what will\", \"happens if\"]):\n            return self._query_impact(entity, top_k)\n        # \"what does X depend on\" / \"what caused X\" → causes (what X needs)\n        elif any(k in q for k in [\"caus\", \"depend on\", \"prereq\", \"needed\", \"require\"]):\n            return self._query_causes(entity, top_k)\n        else:\n            # Default to impact query\n            return self._query_impact(entity, top_k)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35036,"output":960,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48615,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774217106938}}
