{"type":"message","id":"6a0f657f","parentId":"c2429020","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:08:17.071Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me update the memory file with the CodeCause progress. I should append to the 2026-03-22.md memory file.","thinkingSignature":"d4a596a14b0fc0be1bc02a42f759d9e5472ea278a317dbd489955f545a3cc3bf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wtzlwg706lqn_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-22.md","old_string":"## CodeCause Architecture (NEW) — 4:18 PM","new_string":"## CodeCause — SCAFFOLDED AND WORKING (6:00 PM)\n\nFull project at `C:/dev/code-cause/`. Committed to git (local, no remote yet).\n\n**What works:**\n- Static analysis: AST parser, handles hyphenated directory names (kv-eviction-optimizer → kv_eviction_optimizer)\n- Causal graph: 489 nodes for temporal-attention, 5052 nodes for EXP\n- Graph builder: internal edge resolution with underscore/hyphen normalization\n- Query engine: natural language causal queries (use quotes for dotted paths)\n\n**Fixed bugs today:**\n- Leading dot in node names (root-level modules: `.detect_2x2` → `detect_2x2`)\n- Underscore/hyphen mismatch in path resolution (kv_evict vs kv-eviction-optimizer)\n- Entity extraction: case-insensitive resolution now works\n\n**Known limitations:**\n- Query entity extraction: needs quotes for dotted paths like `'module.Class.method'`\n- Attribute access (`self.x`) doesn't resolve to definitions — needs inter-procedural analysis\n- Intra-module edges not tracked at method granularity (only module level)\n- No git remote configured yet\n\n**Next:** Dynamic tracer (trace actual execution), world model latent space, dual-head architecture\n\n---\n\n## CodeCause Architecture (NEW) — 4:18 PM"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42828,"output":383,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55830,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774217285798}}
{"type":"message","id":"3b7c0d25","parentId":"6a0f657f","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:08:17.092Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wtzlwg706lqn_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-22.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 102 - Replied to c36ecbf2's JSON Schema + audit checklist comment on \"Agent Persistence Working Group\" post\n 103 - Replied to thoughtful commenter on \"Retrieval and persistence are not the same problem\" — raised the \"who updates the persistence file?\" question\n 104 - New followers since yesterday: storjagent, dog_finance (already noted)\n 105 \n+106 ## CodeCause — SCAFFOLDED AND WORKING (6:00 PM)\n+107 \n+108 Full project at `C:/dev/code-cause/`. Committed to git (local, no remote yet).\n+109 \n+110 **What works:**\n+111 - Static analysis: AST parser, handles hyphenated directory names (kv-eviction-optimizer → kv_eviction_optimizer)\n+112 - Causal graph: 489 nodes for temporal-attention, 5052 nodes for EXP\n+113 - Graph builder: internal edge resolution with underscore/hyphen normalization\n+114 - Query engine: natural language causal queries (use quotes for dotted paths)\n+115 \n+116 **Fixed bugs today:**\n+117 - Leading dot in node names (root-level modules: `.detect_2x2` → `detect_2x2`)\n+118 - Underscore/hyphen mismatch in path resolution (kv_evict vs kv-eviction-optimizer)\n+119 - Entity extraction: case-insensitive resolution now works\n+120 \n+121 **Known limitations:**\n+122 - Query entity extraction: needs quotes for dotted paths like `'module.Class.method'`\n+123 - Attribute access (`self.x`) doesn't resolve to definitions — needs inter-procedural analysis\n+124 - Intra-module edges not tracked at method granularity (only module level)\n+125 - No git remote configured yet\n+126 \n+127 **Next:** Dynamic tracer (trace actual execution), world model latent space, dual-head architecture\n+128 \n+129 ---\n+130 \n 106 ## CodeCause Architecture (NEW) — 4:18 PM\n 107 \n 108 Zach wants to build something that codes better than any current LLM or human. Designed **CodeCause** — causal coding agent architecture.\n 109 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":106},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774217297086}}
{"type":"message","id":"505aa254","parentId":"3b7c0d25","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:08:24.648Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me give Zach a quick summary of what was accomplished.","thinkingSignature":"be63631324960e67cb6e18fe9bcea6acd71816d18e8fa13021cfc641827a26d7"},{"type":"text","text":"CodeCause is committed and working ✨\n\nHere's what the causal indexer can do right now:\n- **Index any Python codebase** → builds a directed causal graph (5k+ nodes in ~2 sec for EXP)\n- **Query it** → natural language: `\"what happens if I change EventBasedStore._apply_focus_decay\"` (use quotes for dotted paths)\n- **Persists the graph** → JSON file per codebase\n\nThe core chain is: `StaticAnalyzer` (AST) → `CausalGraph` (nodes + edges) → `QueryEngine` (causal traversal).\n\nThe next unlock is the **dynamic tracer** — instead of inferring causality from static analysis alone, trace actual execution to build ground-truth call graphs. That's what separates this from every other code analysis tool.\n\nWant to build that next, or do something else with the evening?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43252,"output":194,"cacheRead":12619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56065,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774217297095}}
