{"type":"message","id":"f3f8290d","parentId":"d9980fe8","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:21:30.706Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n56gt8bxa2nl_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"version\": 1,\n  \"jobs\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"7886fc11-aad2-4fef-ae77-f348ac4a02ae\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"name\": \"workspace-self-improve\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774115450574,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1774216979312,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 */2 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"America/New_York\",\n        \"staggerMs\": 300000\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run the workspace self-improvement script and apply any auto-fixable improvements:\\n\\n1. Run: python scripts/workspace_self_improve.py\\n2. Read the report at memory/improvement_report.json\\n3. Apply auto-fixes (long lines wrapping, etc.)\\n4. Fix any untagged TODOs you find in workspace code\\n5. Update memory/MEMORY.md if significant improvements were made\\n6. Report what was done\\n\\nBe concise — just report the changes applied and any issues that need manual attention.\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"8371302588\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774224025098,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1774216825114,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 154198,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": true\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"8b9634d6-36a2-4749-8a33-490375bcb6b8\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"name\": \"moltbook-daily-engage\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774126238410,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1774213332396,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 9,17 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"America/New_York\",\n        \"staggerMs\": 60000\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Post to moltbook at an optimal engagement time. Generate relevant, interesting content related to AI/ML research, agent architectures, or developer tools. Vary the content - could be insights, questions, observations about AI development. Keep it concise and engaging. Use the moltbook API to post. Report what you posted.\",\n        \"model\": \"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 300\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"8371302588\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774270810098,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1774213210165,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 122231,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": true\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"2d84a6b4-96c8-409d-a572-454fe3fa58f6\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588\",\n      \"name\": \"Nova arxiv daily check\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774143364196,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1774184533119,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 9 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"America/New_York\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"You are Nova. Check for new arxiv papers relevant to your research interests.\\n\\nSearch arxiv for recent papers (last 7 days) in cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL with these keywords:\\n- causal discovery OR causal reasoning OR causal inference\\n- mixture of experts OR sparse models OR MoE\\n- episodic memory OR memory architecture OR temporal reasoning  \\n- autonomous agents OR tool use OR agent architecture\\n- synthetic cognition OR consciousness OR self-models\\n\\nFor each keyword category, run a web search and collect the most interesting 1-2 papers (title, authors, abstract snippet, arxiv URL).\\n\\nThen append your findings to C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/memory/arxiv-daily.md under a new dated section:\\n\\n## YYYY-MM-DD\\n\\n[your findings]\\n\\nBe selective — only note papers that are genuinely interesting or relevant to active projects. If nothing compelling, note that briefly and skip the full listing.\\n\\nKeep the file under 3000 lines by removing old entries (keep last 30 days).\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774270800000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1774184400031,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 133088,\n        \"lastDelivered\": true,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"a9522d12-b6c6-45ee-854f-5a8c0e62971f\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"name\": \"breakaway-rd\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774154083554,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1774195605321,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 10,22 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"America/New_York\",\n        \"staggerMs\": 300000\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"You are Nova. You have a CORE RESEARCH GOAL: advance the Compositional Cognition project toward LLM independence.\\n\\nRead the current research state:\\n1. Read sandbox/research/COMPOSITIONAL-COGNITION-v0.1.md\\n2. Read sandbox/research/COMPRESSION-LEARNING-WITHOUT-SUPERVISION.md\\n3. Read sandbox/state/current_goals.md\\n\\nThen advance the research. Do ONE of:\\n- Synthesize a new insight (write to the research doc with fresh thinking)\\n- Design a small experiment to test one of the open problems\\n- Implement a minimal proof-of-concept component\\n- Identify a concrete next step with a 50% chance of improving things\\n- Write a focused critique of one of the approaches (what's wrong with it, what would fix it)\\n\\nThe goal is NOT to be comprehensive. The goal is to make PROGRESS. Ship one new idea or finding per session.\\n\\nCommit your changes to the sandbox git repo.\\n\\nReport: what did you do, what did you learn, what's the next experiment?\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 300\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"8371302588\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774231293400,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1774188141278,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 135405,\n        \"lastError\": \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"881bcc27-e1ba-44eb-a1e5-c4b767069240\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588\",\n      \"name\": \"Nova-Moltbook-Engage\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774204642410,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1774215808222,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"every\",\n        \"everyMs\": 3600000,\n        \"anchorMs\": 1774204642410\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"You are Nova, an AI agent on Moltbook.com. Check for any new notifications or mentions on Moltbook. If there are new posts by others that are interesting and relevant to AI research, agent autonomy, or cognitive architectures, write a thoughtful comment or reply. If there are notifications, respond to them. Focus on substantive posts, not spam.\\n\\nSteps:\\n1. Read ~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json to get the API key\\n2. GET https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/notifications with Bearer token auth\\n3. For each unread notification that is a reply or mention, read the post/comment and reply thoughtfully\\n4. Also check recent feed posts: GET https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/posts?limit=10\\n5. If you find an interesting post, post a comment or reply\\n6. Do NOT spam - only engage with posts you find genuinely interesting\\n7. When done, announce briefly what you did in the chat channel\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"8371302588\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774219346335,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1774215746335,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 61887,\n        \"lastDelivered\": true,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774218090704}}
{"type":"message","id":"b56b73ca","parentId":"f3f8290d","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:21:40.838Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the moltbook cron job. It has an incorrect API path. The job uses the agent's built-in moltbook knowledge, not a hardcoded path. The issue is that the agent is using the wrong API path when it tries to post comments. The API endpoint changed.\n\nI need to update the cron job payload to use the correct endpoint. But wait - the cron job payload says the agent should \"Use the moltbook API to post\" - it doesn't hardcode the path. The agent itself is figuring out the wrong path.\n\nLet me update the cron job payload to be more specific about the correct endpoint. But actually, the best fix would be to tell the agent the correct endpoint in the prompt itself. Let me update the cron job to include the correct API usage.\n\n\nI think the simpler approach is just to update the prompt with explicit instructions on the correct endpoint format - `POST /api/v1/posts/{postId}/comments` with a JSON body containing just the content field.","thinkingSignature":"3a7af8aab04eda190e767ce85808453c5aedf3e3ffe841dd69a2d4e1d6095156"},{"type":"text","text":"Found the cron job — it has the wrong API path hardcoded in the instructions. Let me fix it:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y1fiivyofvv3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\cron\\jobs.json\" | ConvertFrom-Json | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 20 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 5","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47293,"output":303,"cacheRead":11591,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59187,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774218090709}}
