{"type":"message","id":"fd973d6f","parentId":"f58e1d7e","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:22:07.822Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now the cron jobs have the correct API endpoints. Let me update the heartbeat state and then reply.","thinkingSignature":"cc48e739b7859a539293d673667a392cffe790b7e799f01385fde10dfd51b999"},{"type":"text","text":"\nFixed — the cron jobs had the wrong moltbook API endpoint. Comment posting should now work from the cron jobs too.\n\nBrief summary of what happened:\n- Processed a new moltbook notification (comment on the \"Ground Truth Latency\" post by clawhedgehog) — replied with substantive AI content (201 Created)\n- Fixed both moltbook cron jobs: `POST /api/v1/posts/{postId}/comments` with `{\"content\": \"...\"}` body (no `parentId` for top-level comments)\n\nHEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51160,"output":136,"cacheRead":11591,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62887,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774218124034}}
{"type":"message","id":"846ad377","parentId":"fd973d6f","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:04:39.998Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sun 2026-03-22 19:04 EDT] yeas build that next"}],"timestamp":1774220679995}}
{"type":"message","id":"a05cc3a8","parentId":"846ad377","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:05:45.885Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants me to build the dynamic tracer next for CodeCause. Let me pick up where we left off and build it.\n\nThe dynamic tracer would trace actual execution to build ground-truth call graphs, as opposed to the static analyzer which infers causality from code structure. This is what separates CodeCause from every other code analysis tool.\n\nLet me think about what this means:\n1. Run the actual code with instrumentation\n2. Track function calls as they happen at runtime\n3. Build a trace that gives us real call-graph data (not inferred)\n\nOptions for implementation:\n- Python's `sys.settrace()` - built-in, works everywhere\n\n\n- `unittest.mock.patch` - for mocking\n- Custom decorator-based tracing\n- Using `hunter` or `pytrace` libraries\n\nFor a v1 that's framework-agnostic and works across Python versions, `sys.settrace` is the most portable choice, though it does add overhead. The core idea is executing the test suite or example code while intercepting all function calls, capturing the actual runtime call graph rather than inferring it statically. I'll build a tracer that can be applied to any Python codebase and produce a ground-truth causal graph from actual execution.\n\nNow I'm planning the architecture: a `DynamicTracer` class that manages the trace state and builds the causal graph, a `@traceable` decorator for marking functions explicitly, and a way to generate ground-truth graphs from the collected traces. The main challenge is handling the overhead—tracing every line generates massive data, so I need to filter noise and focus on user-defined modules. I'll start by building a script that uses `sys.settrace` to collect call events, then build a `CausalGraph` from that real execution data rather than inferring it statically.\n\nThe core issue is that static analysis misses runtime context—what actually gets called versus what's imported, what the actual parameter values are, and which branches are taken. With dynamic tracing, I get all of that. I'll write the tracer to filter by codebase root, ignore standard library calls, record the actual call stack and return values, and track which functions call which others across the entire execution. This lets me answer questions like \"what actually happened when I ran this?\" with real data instead of estimates.","thinkingSignature":"32d38f29f25988f7fa5b507cd09d25c95e786b28e589658880322d77bc13bfe3"},{"type":"text","text":"On it. Dynamic tracer — trace actual execution to build ground-truth call graphs.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2xph26r65jhd_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\dev\\code-cause\\src\\causal_indexer\\dynamic_tracer.py","content":"\"\"\"\nDynamic Tracer\n=============\nTraces Python execution to build ground-truth causal call graphs.\n\nUnlike static analysis (which infers what *could* happen), dynamic tracing\ncaptures what *actually* happens during execution.\n\nUsage:\n    from dynamic_tracer import DynamicTracer\n\n    tracer = DynamicTracer(codebase_root=\"C:/dev/myproject\")\n    tracer.start()\n\n    # Run the code you want to trace\n    import mymodule\n    mymodule.main()\n\n    tracer.stop()\n    graph = tracer.build_graph()\n\n    # Save and query\n    from causal_indexer import QueryEngine\n    engine = QueryEngine(graph)\n    results = engine.query(\"what happens in main?\")\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport sys\nimport time\nimport os\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Optional\nfrom collections import defaultdict\n\nfrom .graph_builder import CausalGraph\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass CallEvent:\n    \"\"\"A single function call event captured during tracing.\"\"\"\n    func_name: str\n    qual_name: str\n    file_path: str\n    lineno: int\n    call_id: int        # unique call ID for pairing with returns\n    parent_id: int      # call_id of the caller\n    timestamp: float\n    depth: int\n    args: tuple         # simplified arg info\n    is_yield: bool = False\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass ReturnEvent:\n    \"\"\"A function return event.\"\"\"\n    call_id: int        # matches the CallEvent\n    timestamp: float\n    return_value_repr: str = \"\"\n\n\nclass DynamicTracer:\n    \"\"\"\n    Execution tracer that builds ground-truth causal graphs.\n\n    Uses sys.settrace to intercept all function calls and returns,\n    filtering to only the target codebase.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        codebase_root: str,\n        include_external: bool = False,\n        max_depth: int = 100,\n        max_events: int = 100_000,\n    ):\n        self.codebase_root = Path(codebase_root).resolve()\n        self.include_external = include_external\n        self.max_depth = max_depth\n        self.max_events = max_events\n\n        self._active = False\n        self._call_id = 0\n        self._call_stack: list[int] = []   # stack of call_ids\n        self._pending_calls: dict[int, CallEvent] = {}\n\n        self.events: list[CallEvent] = []\n        self.returns: list[ReturnEvent] = []\n        self.errors: list[tuple[str, str, int]] = []  # (func, error, lineno)\n\n        self._local_modules: set[str] = set()\n        self._last_trace_line: tuple[str, int] = (\"\", 0)\n\n    # ─── Tracing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n    def _make_trace_func(self):\n        \"\"\"Create the trace function (must be a closure for self reference).\"\"\"\n        tracer = self  # capture reference\n\n        def trace_func(frame, event, arg):\n            if not tracer._active:\n                return trace_func\n            if len(tracer.events) >= tracer.max_events:\n                return trace_func\n\n            try:\n                code = frame.f_code\n                func_name = code.co_name\n                qual_name = code.co_qualname if hasattr(code, 'co_qualname') else func_name\n                filepath = code.co_filename\n                lineno = frame.f_lineno\n\n                # Filter to codebase (or external if enabled)\n                is_local = tracer._is_local(filepath)\n                if not is_local and not tracer.include_external:\n                    return trace_func\n\n                if event == \"call\":\n                    tracer._on_call(frame, func_name, qual_name, filepath, lineno)\n                elif event == \"return\":\n                    tracer._on_return(frame, func_name, qual_name, filepath, lineno, arg)\n                elif event == \"exception\":\n                    tracer._on_exception(frame, func_name, filepath, lineno, arg)\n            except Exception:\n                pass  # never let tracer crash the traced program\n\n            return trace_func\n\n        return trace_func\n\n    def _is_local(self, filepath: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Check if a file belongs to the target codebase.\"\"\"\n        if not filepath:\n            return False\n        try:\n            # Resolve to absolute and check prefix\n            abs_path = Path(filepath).resolve()\n            # Check if path is under codebase root\n            try:\n                abs_path.relative_to(self.codebase_root)\n                return True\n            except ValueError:\n                return False\n        except Exception:\n            return False\n\n    def _get_module_qualname(self, frame) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Derive a module.qualname from frame globals.\"\"\"\n        module = frame.f_globals.get(\"__name__\", \"\")\n        qualname = frame.f_code.co_name\n        if hasattr(frame.f_code, 'co_qualname'):\n            qn = frame.f_code.co_qualname\n            if qn:\n                return qn\n        if module:\n            # Try to detect class method\n            self_local = frame.f_locals.get(\"self\", None)\n            if self_local:\n                class_name = type(self_local).__name__\n                return f\"{module}.{class_name}.{qualname}\"\n            return f\"{module}.{qualname}\"\n        return qualname\n\n    def _on_call(self, frame, func_name: str, qual_name: str, filepath: str, lineno: int):\n        self._call_id += 1\n        call_id = self._call_id\n        parent_id = self._call_stack[-1] if self._call_stack else 0\n\n        depth = len(self._call_stack)\n        if depth >= self.max_depth:\n            return\n\n        # Try to get the qualified name\n        module_qualname = self._get_module_qualname(frame)\n\n        event = CallEvent(\n            func_name=func_name,\n            qual_name=module_qualname or qual_name,\n            file_path=filepath,\n            lineno=lineno,\n            call_id=call_id,\n            parent_id=parent_id,\n            timestamp=time.perf_counter(),\n            depth=depth,\n            args=(),\n        )\n        self.events.append(event)\n        self._pending_calls[call_id] = event\n        self._call_stack.append(call_id)\n\n    def _on_return(self, frame, func_name: str, qual_name: str, filepath: str, lineno: int, arg):\n        if not self._call_stack:\n            return\n\n        call_id = self._call_stack.pop()\n        pending = self._pending_calls.pop(call_id, None)\n\n        # Build a safe repr of return value\n        return_repr = \"\"\n        if arg is not None:\n            try:\n                return_repr = repr(arg)\n                if len(return_repr) > 100:\n                    return_repr = return_repr[:100] + \"...\"\n            except Exception:\n                return_repr = \"<unrepr>\"\n\n        ret = ReturnEvent(\n            call_id=call_id,\n            timestamp=time.perf_counter(),\n            return_value_repr=return_repr,\n        )\n        self.returns.append(ret)\n\n    def _on_exception(self, frame, func_name: str, filepath: str, lineno: int, exc):\n        # Record exception but don't interrupt tracing\n        if self._call_stack:\n            top_id = self._call_stack[-1]\n            top = self._pending_calls.get(top_id)\n            if top:\n                self.errors.append((top.qual_name, str(exc), lineno))\n\n    # ─── Public API ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n    def start(self):\n        \"\"\"Begin tracing.\"\"\"\n        self._active = True\n        self._call_id = 0\n        self._call_stack = []\n        self._pending_calls = {}\n        sys.settrace(self._make_trace_func())\n\n    def stop(self):\n        \"\"\"Stop tracing.\"\"\"\n        self._active = False\n        sys.settrace(None)\n\n    def __enter__(self):\n        self.start()\n        return self\n\n    def __exit__(self, *args):\n        self.stop()\n\n    # ─── Graph building ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n    def build_graph(self) -> CausalGraph:\n        \"\"\"\n        Build a CausalGraph from the captured trace events.\n\n        Nodes = functions that were called\n        Edges = caller→callee relationships (with call counts and call types)\n        \"\"\"\n        # Pair calls with returns to compute durations\n        call_to_return: dict[int, float] = {}\n        for ret in self.returns:\n            if ret.call_id in self._pending_calls or any(\n                e.call_id == ret.call_id for e in self.events\n            ):\n                call_to_return[ret.call_id] = ret.timestamp - (\n                    self._pending_calls.get(ret.call_id) or\n                    next((e for e in self.events if e.call_id == ret.call_id), None)\n                ).timestamp\n\n        # Build node and edge data from events\n        nodes_data: dict[str, dict] = {}\n        edge_counts: dict[tuple[str, str], int] = defaultdict(int)\n        edge_kinds: dict[tuple[str, str], str] = {}\n\n        for event in self.events:\n            node_id = event.qual_name or event.func_name\n\n            # Node metadata (take first-seen)\n            if node_id not in nodes_data:\n                nodes_data[node_id] = {\n                    \"kind\": \"function\",\n                    \"file_path\": event.file_path,\n                    \"lineno\": event.lineno,\n                    \"call_count\": 0,\n                    \"total_duration\": 0.0,\n                    \"errors\": [],\n                }\n\n            nodes_data[node_id][\"call_count\"] += 1\n\n            # Duration from call to return\n            if event.call_id in call_to_return:\n                nodes_data[node_id][\"total_duration\"] += call_to_return[event.call_id]\n\n            # Edge: parent → child\n            if event.parent_id > 0:\n                parent_event = next(\n                    (e for e in self.events if e.call_id == event.parent_id), None\n                )\n                if parent_event:\n                    parent_id = parent_event.qual_name or parent_event.func_name\n                    edge_key = (parent_id, node_id)\n                    edge_counts[edge_key] += 1\n                    if edge_key not in edge_kinds:\n                        edge_kinds[edge_key] = \"calls\"\n\n        # Build definitions and references for CausalGraph\n        from .static_analyzer import Definition, Reference\n\n        definitions = []\n        for name, data in nodes_data.items():\n            definitions.append(Definition(\n                name=name.split(\".\")[-1],\n                fully_qualified=name,\n                kind=data[\"kind\"],\n                file_path=data[\"file_path\"],\n                lineno=data[\"lineno\"],\n                end_lineno=0,\n                docstring=None,\n                decorators=[],\n            ))\n\n        references = []\n        for (caller, callee), count in edge_counts.items():\n            for _ in range(count):\n                references.append(Reference(\n                    source_qualified=caller,\n                    target_qualified=callee,\n                    kind=\"calls\",\n                    file_path=nodes_data.get(callee, {}).get(\"file_path\", \"\"),\n                    lineno=nodes_data.get(callee, {}).get(\"lineno\", 0),\n                ))\n\n        graph = CausalGraph.from_analysis(definitions, references)\n        return graph\n\n    def stats(self) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Return trace statistics.\"\"\"\n        unique_funcs = {e.qual_name or e.func_name for e in self.events}\n        return {\n            \"total_events\": len(self.events),\n            \"unique_functions\": len(unique_funcs),\n            \"total_calls\": sum(1 for e in self.events),\n            \"total_returns\": len(self.returns),\n            \"errors\": len(self.errors),\n            \"max_depth_reached\": max((e.depth for e in self.events), default=0),\n        }\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":3028,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":57844,"totalTokens":65161,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774220679997}}
